This paper deals with word association measures and their performance evaluation through experiments with publicly available datasets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) sub-category of Computer Science, which is cs.CL. Additionally, the paper involves the use of co-occurrence based measures, which are commonly used in Information Retrieval (IR) and Machine Learning (ML) tasks. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of resource-heavy distributional similarity and knowledge-based word association measures, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Data Science (DS) tasks. Hence, cs.AI and cs.DS are also likely sub-categories.
